CONFIRMED genuine skip (#3) — needs the removed embedded-Python `self`/interpreter.this binding.

test.ngc uses inline `;py,` blocks and Python O-word subs to store an arbitrary
attribute on the interpreter object (o<retainparam1> does `self.param1 = x`) and
read it back later — both through another o-word (o<checkparam1_retained>) and via
`;py,assert interpreter.this.param1 == 25.0`, verifying that the handler `self` is
aliased to the module-level `interpreter.this` and that attributes persist on it.

gomc removed the embedded Python interpreter. The C interp_ext handlers are
stateless C callbacks — there is no interpreter-bound Python `self` to attach
attributes to, and no `interpreter.this` alias, so this has no equivalent. (A cmod
could keep its own state, but that would not test the Python self/this aliasing the
test exists to check.) Genuine removal.
